107. Powers of Appellate Court.__(1) Subject to such conditions and limitations as may beprescribed, an Appellate Court shall have power__
(a) to determine a case finally;
(b) to remand a case;
(c) to frame issues and refer them for trial;
(d) to take additional evidence or to require such evidence to be taken.

