238. When offence proved included in offence charged.(1) When a person is charged with an offenceconsisting of several particulars, a combination of some only of which constitutes, a complete minoroffence, and such combination is proved, that the remaining particulars are not proved, he may be convictedof the minor offence, though he was not charged with it.
(2) When a person is charged with an offence and facts are proved which reduce it to a minor offence,he may be convicted of the minor offence, although he is not charged with it.

